    "body": "- `nvim --version`:\r\n```\r\nNVIM v0.2.1\r\nBuild type: Release\r\nLuaJIT 2.0.5\r\nCompilation: /usr/local/Homebrew/Library/Homebrew/shims/super/clang -Wconversion -U_FORTIFY_SOURCE -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=1 -DNVIM_MSGPACK_HAS_FLOAT32 -DNVIM_UNIBI_HAS_VAR_FROM -DNDEBUG -DMIN_LOG_LEVEL=3 -Wall -Wextra -pedantic -Wno-unused-parameter -Wstrict-prototypes -std=gnu99 -Wimplicit-fallthrough -Wvla -fstack-protector-strong -fdiagnostics-color=auto -DINCLUDE_GENERATED_DECLARATIONS -I/tmp/neovim-20171109-46118-9kky38/neovim-0.2.1/build/config -I/tmp/neovim-20171109-46118-9kky38/neovim-0.2.1/src -I/usr/local/include -I/usr/local/include -I/usr/local/include -I/usr/local/include -I/usr/local/include -I/usr/local/include -I/usr/local/opt/gettext/include -I/usr/include -I/tmp/neovim-20171109-46118-9kky38/neovim-0.2.1/build/src/nvim/auto -I/tmp/neovim-20171109-46118-9kky38/neovim-0.2.1/build/include\r\nKompilerad av brew@Sierra.local\r\n```\r\n- Vim (version: ) behaves differently? Yes, vim gives an option to delete the file\r\n- Operating system/version: OSX\r\n- Terminal name/version: fish/bash/zsh\r\n- `$TERM`: screen-256color\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\nOpen a file which is already open/has crashed and left the swap file.\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\nNeovim gives no option to delete the file and start editing the file.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nAn option to delete the swap file and immediately start editing it.\r\n\r\nPerhaps this is intentional and one is suppose to delete it manually? But if that is the case then there is a separate issue in that the path displayed to the swap file is wrong.\r\n\r\n```\r\nUsers/user/.local/share/nvim/swap//%Users%username%Code%src%lib.rs.swp\r\n//                               ^ Extra / here\r\n\r\nUsers/user/.local/share/nvim/swap/%Users%username%Code%src%lib.rs.swp\r\n```\r\n\r\nThird, a minor papercut. I use https://fishshell.com which is addmittedly non-standard but I will mention the papercut anyway. The use of `%` in the path does not play well with it as `%` needs to be escaped in the path which prevents the path from being copy-pasted :/",
