            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Can you paste the exact message? Normally both Vim and Neovim refer to an already-open process which is supposed to be “the other editor instance editing the same file” if they do not give the option.\r\n\r\nThough I must say that neither actually do check whether the mentioned process belongs to Vim/Neovim and process identifiers are being reused: AFAIK the judjment is that the process of checking process name given PID is highly system-dependent, may be forbidden or outright wrong (I mean the case when checking process name gives result which could not possibly have anything to do with the source of the PID being checked: PID namespaces, just NFS with users from different machines, …) and the event in which PID is reused while being not unlikely is not too often to worth the hassle.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nAs for “papercut”: shells are normally configurable, if it was zsh I would say for sure you can create a keyboard shortcut which does escape pasting, and, probably, after learning how url-quote-magic and bracketed-paste-magic work, make that automatic on regular paste (though I would not normally bother as shortcut is much simpler). And it is not like we have many options here given that maximal path length is limited and different shells have loads of different special characters, some even controlled by an option (e.g. I can make zsh use `%` for history expansion in place of `!`). (And we cannot escape the path for pasting as well, nobody knows where you paste to.)",
